// Gate-1b0: the first-ever test of the failing-assert path. The interpreter
// errors cleanly (exit 1, "assert_eq failed: 1 != 2"); the JIT now routes
// IrTerminator::Trap through the cx_trap host callback and exits cleanly
// (code 126) too. Before Gate-1b0 the JIT stack-overflowed here (0xC00000FD) —
// the bug hid because every other assert fixture passes, so the trap path was
// never exercised. Both backends reject with a non-zero exit → convergent PASS.
// Operands are variables so the inequality reaches runtime, not semantic time.
a: t64 = 1
b: t64 = 2
assert_eq(a, b)
